name: Watermelon
description: Watermelon is a watery fruit that grows in the vine-like shrub flowering plant that comes from the family Cucurbitaceae and contains water. The color of the outer shell is green and thick, and the inner fleshy part is red.

name: Apple
description: An apple is an edible fruit that is cultivated worldwide from the species Malus. This fruit contains vital minerals, vitamins, and other nutrients, which are beneficial for our body. Its color is red, pink, green, and has a sweet taste.

name: Banana
description: A banana is a fleshy and edible fruit that does not contain any seeds. Its family is Musa named scientifically, Musa acuminate, variable in size, color, and elongated, curve-shaped. It is all fleshy and sweet, full of starch, and is green, yellow, red, purple, or brown when ripened. This is also used as a vegetable when it is raw, called plantains.

name: Cherry
description: Cherry is a fruit of genus prunus, is a fleshy drupe. The sweet cherry is scientifically named Prunus avium, and the sour cherry is named Prunus cerasus. It is red, green, orange in colors, and produced in the flowering plants. It is also called cherry blossom and ornamental cherry.

name: Grapes
description: Grape is a berry-type fruit that is used to make wines and is grown on the flowering plant from the Vitis family. It is green in color and a non-climatic type of fruit. Its seeds are used to extract raisins, vinegar, and grape seed oil.

name: Mango
description: The mango is an edible fruit rich in vitamins(A, C &D), and the taste is either sweet when ripe and sour when before ripen. This fruit is also called the king of all fruits, scientifically called Mangifera indica, mostly cultivated in tropical areas.

name: Guava
description: Guava is a fleshy fruit containing seeds inside it, which have vitamin-C rich and a lot of antioxidants, potassium, and fiber. It can be considered as beneficial fruit eaten regularly helps in blood sugar levels and some other purposes. The scientific name for this is Psidium guajava.

name: Lemon
description: Lemon is a fruit, also known as lime, a citrus fruit that contains citric acid in it. This is the same as that of the orange, grapefruit, etc. It is round, green, contains acidic juice vesicles.
